item.title: BOOK. I
item.description: PROP. XX. – THEOREM. The sum of any two sides (BA, AC) of a triangle (ABC) is greater than the third. PROP. XIX. – THEOREM. If one angle (B) of a triangle (ABC) be greater than another angle (C), the side (AC) which it opposite to the greater angle is greater than the side (AB) which is opposite to the less.
